message:
fan spins for a second then shuts off

corrosion around u7400 area 
mostly between u7400 and c7400

tried replacing u7400 with a known good. no change.
all_sys_pwrgd is 0v

r8168 is 99oms
noticed that if r8168 is removed then all_sys_pwrgd is 3.3v and fan stays on
still no chime or image on screen tho.

Problem on DDR power supply.
Its power good pulls down to ground ALL_SYS_PWRGD.

Post resistance to ground at L7430 and some voltages for U7400; pins 6, 12, 16, 17.
Be sure R/C7425 and traces are good.
You may need to change U7400 and/or Q7430...

L7430 pin1 0.7K ohms
L7430 pin2 0.7K ohms

U7400 pin6 0v
U7400 pin12 5v
?????U7400 pin16 0v
U7400 pin17 22.8mV

from c7425 to r7425 is OL.

"from c7425 to r7425 is OL."
Do you mean no connection between R/C7425???

"?????U7400 pin16 0v"
Check voltage on both sides of R8111...

sorry for late reply. 
yes fromc7425 to r7425 there is no connection
voltage is 0v on both sides of r8111

As per schematic R/C7425 are both connected; supposedly corroded trace in your case.
Be aware, Q7430 gets usually fried in such case...
